---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="AI platform docs"
  description="Run Thumbrella through hosted AI platforms like Replicate when that matches your workflow."
>
  <Section
    eyebrow="ai platforms"
    title="Use hosted AI platforms when that is already your deployment model"
    lede="Choose this path when your team already provisions workloads through marketplaces like Replicate or similar hosted AI platforms and wants Thumbrella in the same flow."
  >
    <ol>
      <li>Use the platform account and billing model you already operate with.</li>
      <li>Run the published Thumbrella workload with your media input.</li>
      <li>Account for the platform's own usage fees in your deployment plan.</li>
    </ol>
    <pre><code>replicate run peter/thumbrella input=https://example.com/media.mp4</code></pre>
    <p>
      Thumbrella does not add an extra charge in this mode, but the platform you deploy on still
      charges for its own execution and storage model. This route makes sense when marketplace-based
      operations matter more than running the binary or Docker image directly.
    </p>
  </Section>
</MainLayout>